sql:
SELECT mo.model_name, sd.sale_price
FROM models mo
INNER JOIN sales_data sd ON mo.model_id = sd.model_id;

SELECT model_id, model_name, price
FROM models
WHERE price > (
    SELECT AVG(price)
    FROM models
);

SELECT m.model_name, man.manufacturer_name, m.safety_rating
FROM models m
INNER JOIN manufacturers man ON m.manufacturer_id = man.manufacturer_id;

external_knowledge:
- "Blooming" metaphorically represents sales activity;
- "Month of February" refers to sales data where the sale date is in February;
- The "average price they blossomed at" is the average sale price of each model in February;
- "Total number of blooms" signifies the total quantity of each model sold.

